// GOOD: 2-pass scheme (self/codegen/ir_to_arm64.hexa)
// Pass 1: walk blocks, compute ira_ops_size(op, is_imm, imm, has_cmp)
//         per op — variable because:
//           load_imm:  1 if |imm|<=65535 else 2 (MOVZ + MOVK)
//           sub:       1 alone, 2 when followed by CSET (CMP+CSET)
//           branch:    3 (CMP + B.cond + B)
//           ret:       2 (MOV x0,Rv + RET)
//         Record block_id → starting instruction index.
// Pass 2: re-walk and emit bytes; branch/jump offsets are now the
//         difference of pass-1 indices × 4 bytes.

